<div id="outline-container-sec-1-2" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="sec-1-2"><span class="section-number-3">1.2</span> Representation</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-1-2">
<p>
Given an input space vector \(X\) and an output space vector \(Y\), the hypothesis function \(h(x)\) is the best mapping from the input to the output \(h:X \rightarrow Y\).<br  />
As the figure indicates, the goal is to fing the best hypothesis function for any given input and output set of data.<br  />
</p>
<img src="../img/01hypothesis.png">
<p>
Fig.1: Training model to find h(x) (courtesy of Coursera)<br  />
</p>
</div>
